Other vitamin C products' style='color:blue;' target='_blank'&gt;Vitamin C, chemically referred to as ascorbic acid, is the most important water-soluble antioxidant. Humans have to get vitamin C from their diet because they lack the enzyme L-gluconolactone oxidase, which is required for the synthesis of ascorbic acid, due to a genetic defect. Nature&amp;
